This is my rendition of the Shadow Moses Island Nuclear Waste Disposal Facility from Metal Gear: Solid. Note that it is in the Beta state. I am looking for advice from testers, and am still in the process of optimization. Currently it is a bomb map. There is one game-play flaw that I am familiar with: the fact that the Tank hanger acts as a crunch point (only two main entrances). This is unavoidable, for that is how the level is in mgs. Recommendations accepted.
Update: File has been optimized, details have been added, 3d skybox added, crunch point problem improved, background sounds added, environmental lighting added, colour correction improved.

Map Created by: Silent Ricochet Map Based on: The ruins, by Zipper Interactive for Socom: U.S. Navy SEALs Custom Models and Materials by: Shiroko and Silent Ricochet There are two bomb sites just like the original map. Everything is almost an exact replica of the original map on SOCOM. People who have played the SOCOM version should have no trouble navigating this map. This is a beta version of the map, I'm trying to figure out how to prevent the terrorists from spawning with the bomb, to force them to pick it up in the middle (where it lies for testing purposes). The map does in fact come with a custom Navigation mesh so bots shouldn't have a hard time playing along, besides two minor errors that cannot be fixed because my CSS crashes when I try to edit those particular areas. Have Fun :)
Change Log
  • Changed Lighting
  • Changed Foliage Models (they were fullbright and looked terrible)
  • Optimized the hell out of it
  • Added Custom Navigation Mesh
  • Added Soundscapes
  • Added Semi-Expensive Fog / Haze Effects
  • Added 46 Fully-Built-Cubemaps
  • Added 3d Skybox
  • Deleted Unseen displacement faces (which sometimes caused lighting errors)
  • Fixed Mis-Aligned Textures
  • Fixed Unnecessarily large brushes
  • Fixed some minor brushwork errors (that sometimes hindered movement)

There are three secret doors.  One is in the abandoned room (lower floor by T spawn).  There is a button to open it behind the third shelf from the left (you will notice sparks).  If you run straight through it, there is a teleporter that will return you back outside the door.  To pass it, jump to the edge inside, or sit on the box, shoot the button, and enter on the right side of the secret door.  The second secret door has a similar button just beyond that point, which opens up right into the bomb site.  The final secret door isn't as secretive--it takes you from the warehouse to the bomb site, and is textured in a way that you will notice it anyway.

Hi everyone. This is my very first map made completely from scratch for CSS. I just started mapping last week. :-) - This map has 3 floors: bottom (lounge type), 1st (office type), 2nd (lounge), 3rd (roof). There is indeed a secret room in this map.. there is a door on the 2nd floor but its locked. Somewhere in the map there is a hidden button. Find the hidden button to unlock the door. Inside the secret room there is buttons to control lighting, and a button to lock the door. There are also 5 buttons & a monitor to view areas of this map. There are 2 bombsites, 1 sort of hidden and 1 on the roof. I tried my best to make this map look good, be fun, and be fair to both teams. I hope they are. Well, I hope you enjoy this map, please don't be too hard on me cause it is my first map and there are some problems I couldn't fix.

Welcome to the new FPS gaming sandman css map!

I created the sandman map as a break from the repetitive comp matches and to have some fun with my friends. Here is the css little brother. here a brief description of the map as a whole and the method of gameplay.
Sandman is a bomb defusal map with a twist in the shape of a huge pyarmid and a huge red X on the top. The terrorists try to get to the top of the pyramid to plant the bomb and the counter-terrorists try and stop them. It's not as easy as that though as it takes a fair amount of time to jump over each step and multiple angles to get shot in the back of the head. There are four ladders on each corner of the map that leads to a ledge going round the whole of the map and many boxes to hide behind.

This is just an experiment. I wondered what the world would be like if everything was suddenly flipped. Of course, it costs too much to do it to real life, so I had to settle with de_dust 2.

It's distorting. Confusing. Although it's exactly the same map to play, it feels different. Some people might hate it. Others might find it breathes a new lease of life into an excellent, albeit overplayed map.

Obviously I don't claim to have made it. All I did was to flip it, then fix the displacements, the props that didn't flip properly, and then I finished it off by lining the skybox up again and enduring a lengthy compile time. Once again, I stress that I don't claim to have made this map, though I'm sure that there will be some one who attacks me for passing it off as my own. I don't know if the appeal will wear off straight away or if it will breathe a new lease of life into the map. I'd like to find out.

Oh and I included the original Dust2 as well, with added HDR.

pe_tides_dream is finally done, the third map in the "Dream" series by Privo and Rookie.

You may have played the first two, pe_metal_dream and pe_rust dream, but this map has a completely different and unique style of play.

The first two maps were open, broad, with minimal cover area and lots of ground to cross and snipe. This map is different. Ever play Far Cry? I tried to mimic cover like that. There are bushes, and plants, and rocks for creeping and crawling in. Many times you can simply hide in the bush and jump someone with a knife. It's frantic and quite a bit of fun.

However, an important note is you do not want to play this map with bots. Bots vision is not blocked by the shrubbery in this map, and they will cock you before you even see them. However, with players, it's amazingly fun hiding in the bushes while 4 enemy players run by without noticing you.

The map is small and jam packed with crates, gravestones, fountains, pallets, and even an interior house path that must be broken in two, where two helpless citizens were murdered! (Yes that is my lame excuse for using so many blood decals in the room =)

The map supports over 40 players, and has been fully tested on a live server with 10+ actual people.

If you like this map, please add it to your servers rotation, and possibly check into my two other pe_xxxxx_dream maps.

Add the .bsp to your C:\Steam\SteamApps\username\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps folder.  *SERVER OPERATORS* should also add the map to the servers maps folder, where other custom maps are kept!

Enjoy, and if you have a suggestion for another "Dream" map, send an e-mail away to opticalzero@gmail.com and we'll see if I decide to build on it.
